value.title: Bob Woodward's Donald Trump book 'Rage' sells 600,000 copies in first week
value.excerpt: Bob Woodward's "Rage" sold more than 600,000 copies in its first week of publication, continuing a yearlong wave of blockbuster books about the president. The first week sales include hardcovers, audiobooks and e-books.

value.title: Fact Checkers: On Trade, Trump Has A Large Deficit With The Truth
value.excerpt: A book by Washington Post fact checkers finds many of Trump’s statements on trade may belong in the fiction section of a bookstore.

value.title: Chevron orders staff worldwide to delete WeChat from their work phones, despite a judge blocking Trump's ban of the app
value.excerpt: Chevron has asked staff to delete WeChat off their work phones, despite President Donald Trump's ban on the app being blocked by a federal court.

value.title: Trump said Jews are 'only in it for themselves' and 'stick together,' according to a new report
value.excerpt: The president made the remarks in front of administration officials after a phone call with Jewish lawmakers, according to The Washington Post.

value.title: Trump has 'shady political motives' in blaming China for pandemic, Beijing official says
value.excerpt: The attacks from China's foreign ministry come a day after Trump accused Beijing of allowing the virus to escape its borders and “infect the world.”

value.title: MSNBC’s Donny Deutsch compares Trump to Hitler, blasts Jewish Americans who support him
value.excerpt: MSNBC mainstay Donny Deutsch compared President Trump to Adolf Hitler on Wednesday morning and blasted Jewish Americans who plan to vote for him in November.

value.title: Walmart and Oracle support Trump's idea for TikTok "education fund"
value.excerpt: The financial contribution will come from the new company that emerges from the unusual transaction, called TikTok Global. The arrangement will allow the app to continue operating in the U.S. after the Trump administration threatened to ban it over national security concerns.

value.title: Judd Apatow, Rob Reiner accuse Donald Trump of 'mass murder' in separate tweets
value.excerpt: Filmmakers Judd Apatow and Rob Reiner took to Twitter on Tuesday to accuse Donald Trump of dishonesty and murder.

value.excerpt: Dr. Anthony Fauci, President Donald Trump, actor and producer Michael B. Jordan and rapper Megan Thee Staillion have made this year's TIME 100 list.

value.title: Trump once defined success as keeping US COVID deaths below 200,00. When he failed, he said real failure would be 2.5 million dead.
value.excerpt: Trump in March said fewer than 200,000 dead would show his coronavirus policies had succeeded. He has since changed his opinion.

value.excerpt: Miami-Dade County schools will return to in-person instruction beginning Oct. 14. Donald Trump says U.S. death toll is "a shame." Latest COVID news.

value.title: Trump's campaign blew almost $1 billion, and now it's in deep trouble
value.excerpt: Trump's reelection campaign started the day he was sworn into office, on January 20, 2017. Since then, the campaign has wasted $1 billion.

value.title: Trump Uses E.P.A. Office to Widen ‘Anarchist’ War vs. New York
value.excerpt: The president has painted New York as an “anarchist jurisdiction,” but his administration’s threats to withhold funds are being dismissed as a politicized campaign tactic.

value.title: Fact check: False claim suggesting Trump nominated Biden to the Supreme Court started out as satire
value.excerpt: A false claim posted on social media originated as a satirical article. President Trump has yet to announce his next high court nominee.

value.title: 200,000 dead as Trump vilifies science, prioritizes politics

value.title: Trump went golfing 25 times as a virus swept across the US and killed over 200,000 Americans
value.excerpt: As the virus swept across the US, Trump downplayed the threat, deflected blame to others, and routinely visited his properties to play golf.

value.title: ‘It affects virtually nobody’: Trump downplays virus threat to young people
value.excerpt: The president previously told The Washington Post’s Bob Woodward in March that Covid-19 affects “plenty of young people.”

value.title: Trump Says ‘We Need Nine Justices’ Before Election Day, Justifies by Repeating Conspiracy Theory About Mail-In Ballots

value.title: The Russian Trolls Have a Simpler Job Today. Quote Trump.
value.excerpt: As part of their attempt to interfere with the 2020 election, Russians are grabbing screenshots of President Trump’s tweets, or quoting his own misleading statements, analysts and officials say.

value.title: Cindy McCain endorses Joe Biden in rebuke of President Trump
value.excerpt: Cindy McCain’s backing could help Biden appeal to Republicans disaffected with Trump and give the former VP a boost in Arizona.

value.title: WATCH: Trump Campaign Brags About Crowd of Fans Outside Biden Wisconsin Event — But There Were More Biden Backers
value.excerpt: Trump's campaign posted video bragging about the crowd of supporters outside Joe Biden's Wisconsin event, but local news footage shows there were even more Biden supporters there.

value.title: Trump-Biden debate topics released ahead of their first head-to-head matchup
value.excerpt: The first presidential debate will take place Sept. 29 in Cleveland and will be moderated by Fox News journalist Chris Wallace.

value.title: 'It's a shame.' Trump reacts to COVID-19 death toll hitting 200,000
value.excerpt: Asked about the 200,000 COVID-19 deaths as reported by Johns Hopkins as he left the White House on Tuesday, Trump said "it’s a shame."
